      "side": 1,
      "message": "After this: https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/344759 change landed we were no longer sync\u0027ing between each upload in the ColorTypeBackendAllocationTest. This means that multiple uploads can grab a slice in a xfer buffer, which means the offset alignment starts to matter. The Intel 405 GPU supports R8G8B8 which has a block size of 3. We we\u0027re rounding that up to 4 but we really need a value that is a multiple of 4 and the block size, so 12 in this case. GrStagingBufferManager was using GrAlignTo, which only works with pow2 values.",
